{
  "stem": "3659.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the first time I ate with them was when I was six years old, because we were not permitted at the dining room table unless our manners were impeccable.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were really taught how to eat properly, and it was a very important thing to eat properly and behave yourself at a dinner table.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And most of the conversations were conducted at the dinner table, which really was lunchtime.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Between 12:00 and 2:00 in the afternoon, my father used to come home from business, and we had dinner.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then maybe he took a little nap, and he left again and then didn't return until about 7:30 or 8 o'clock at night.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By that time, most of the time we were either already in bed, or we only had about 5 or 10 minutes to spend with my father.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was one thing that my father always used to preach to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And because, you know, my mother having gone through the pogrom and him also being in Poland and having experienced quite a number of things, he said, the most important thing in life that you can do is further and educate yourself, because they can take any-- everything away from you, all your possessions.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There's one thing they cannot take away, and that's what you have in your brain.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So learn, learn, learn.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was practically preached to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So learning and education was a very important facet in our life and, of course, also the closeness of the Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my mother was really the one that furthered it more so than my father, because, for some reason or the other, the Conservative religious was not his thing, and he turned against it.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
